		"description": "<p>You&rsquo;re always prepared, always ready, always dangerous. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Dexterity or Intelligence score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>Half your scholar levels count as rogue levels for the purpose of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.mc153rkyv5li85dh]{Expert Talent} feature.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with a skill or tool of your choice.</li>\n<li>You gain a number of Preparedness Points equal to your proficiency bonus plus your Intelligence modifier. At the beginning of your turn (no action required), you can spend these at an exchange rate of 1 preparedness point to 25gp to produce a piece of mundane equipment that you conceivably could have purchased for that much or less. The item cannot be bulky. When your rogue and scholar levels total 15, you can also produce common magic items this way. &nbsp;The equipment generated by this benefit is obviously temporary and improvised in nature. It cannot be sold and crumbles to worthless scrap if not used by the start of your next long rest. You regain your preparedness points when you finish a long rest in a haven.</li>\n</ul>",
